Airtel Africa Plc reported a quarterly pretax profit on Friday that more than doubled, as the telecom company signed up more customers for its mobile and data services. The company’s pretax profit for the first quarter rose to $167.4 million from $80.2 million a year ago, boosted by a 9.3 per cent rise in its customer base. Airtel Africa, a unit of India’s Bharti Airtel Ltd debuted on the London Stock Exchange last month.   Amendments that the govt tabled are different from those recommended by the supreme court. Allegations of trying to block the president from running in 2020 saw the sacking of Makamba.